Package me.wobblyyyy.pathfinder.pathfinding.routes.generic

Class GoAndTurn

  • java.lang.Object
    • me.wobblyyyy.pathfinder.pathfinding.routes.HighRoute
      • me.wobblyyyy.pathfinder.pathfinding.routes.generic.GoAndTurn
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Route
    public class GoAndTurn
extends HighRoute
    The most basic of the routes - start by moving to the target position, and then turn after getting there.

    This will probably be used the most frequently, until a go-and-turn at the same time route is developed, which will happen later. For now, however, this is your best bet - I can only assume this will be the most frequently used route.

    Author:
    Colin Robertson
